    "For example, in the first section of contract documents, we always find the object of the contract.",
    "In this scenario, we can assume that the best chunking strategy is to separate the chunks by section of the document.",
    "In this case, the overlap between the chunks occurs by section, since the questions will be answered by information contained in the section itself or in previous or subsequent sections.",
    "For the contract page in the example in Figure?",
    "?, we would have a chunk for the section on the object of the contract, another chunk for the section on the term of the contract, that is, a chunk for each clause of the contract and its surroundings."
